\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22-10020-Compose-advanced-models-with-Create-ML-Components","abstract":[{"text":"Take your custom machine learning models to the next level with Create ML Components. We’ll show you how to work with temporal data like video or audio and compose models that can count repetitive human actions or provide advanced sound classification. We’ll also share best practices on using incremental fitting to speed up model training with new data.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-223-Embracing-Algorithms":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-223-embracing-algorithms","type":"topic","title":"Embracing Algorithms","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-223-Embracing-Algorithms","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"When you imagine building a new app, what do you think about? Models, views, and controllers deserve their prominent place in the design process, but we don’t often give the same attention to the underlying work our apps need to do. Understand how to identify and optimize the algorithms in your app, and discover how implementing algorithms as generic protocol extensions results in efficient, effective, and maintainable code.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode"},"https://github.com/apple/swift-collections/blob/108ac4fa4ef7f2622b97a1f5dd92a3e0c6857c60/Documentation/OrderedDictionary.md":{"title":"OrderedSet<Element: Hashable>","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OrderedSet<Element: Hashable>"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections\/blob\/108ac4fa4ef7f2622b97a1f5dd92a3e0c6857c60\/Documentation\/OrderedDictionary.md","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections\/blob\/108ac4fa4ef7f2622b97a1f5dd92a3e0c6857c60\/Documentation\/OrderedDictionary.md"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10217-Explore-numerical-computing-in-Swift":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10217-explore-numerical-computing-in-swift","title":"Explore numerical computing in Swift","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10217-Explore-numerical-computing-in-Swift","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Meet Swift Numerics: a new Swift package for computational mathematics. Take a tour of the protocols and types available in the package and find out how you can use them to write generic code. We’ll also show you how and when to use the new Float16 type to improve performance and reduce memory usage.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article"},"https://github.com/apple/swift-collections/blob/108ac4fa4ef7f2622b97a1f5dd92a3e0c6857c60/Documentation/Deque.md":{"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections\/blob\/108ac4fa4ef7f2622b97a1f5dd92a3e0c6857c60\/Documentation\/Deque.md","title":"Double-ended queue Deque<Element>","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Double-ended queue "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Deque<Element>"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections\/blob\/108ac4fa4ef7f2622b97a1f5dd92a3e0c6857c60\/Documentation\/Deque.md"},"https://github.com/apple/swift-algorithms":{"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-algorithms","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-algorithms","title":"open-source package","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"open-source package"}]},"https://github.com/apple/swift-collections":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"open-source package","type":"text"}],"type":"link","title":"open-source package","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections"},"https://github.com/apple/swift-algorithms/blob/195e0316d7ba71e134d0f6c677f64b4db6160c46/Guides/Chunked.md":{"title":"chunked(by:), chunked(on:), chunks(ofCount:)","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"chunked(by:)"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"chunked(on:)"